HEADWORD: Bogie
<hw>Bo"gie</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <mark>[A dialectic word.
N. of Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <def>A four-wheeled truck, having a certain
amount of play around a vertical axis, used to support in part a
locomotive on a railway track.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogie engine</ent>⟦br⟧
